    <h1>AI Tools We Actually Use (And the Ones We Dropped)</h1>
    <p>We've tested dozens of AI tools. Most overpromise and underdeliver. Here's what actually survived 3 months of daily use.</p>
    <h2>The Winners</h2>
    <p><strong>Claude 4</strong> - Complex reasoning, coding, and long-form writing. The gold standard for serious work.</p>
    <p><strong>ChatGPT</strong> - General tasks, quick answers, brainstorming. Fast and capable for most everyday needs.</p>
    <p><strong>Perplexity</strong> - Research that actually works. Cites sources, explores topics deeply.</p>
    <h2>The Ones We Dropped</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>"AI Everything" tools that do nothing well</li>
      <li>Writing tools with generic output</li>
      <li>Image generators with limited use cases</li>
    </ul>
